news.title: Telangana HC orders disciplinary action against revenue officials over land acquisition delay
news.para: Disciplinary action against revenue officials concerned for being complacent in acquiring land for the construction of Shivanna Gudem balancing reservoir at Khudabakshpally village, Marriguda mandal, Nalgonda district.

news.title: Property developer booked for duping Bihar woman of Rs 42 lakh
news.para: Dr Rashmi Kumari from Bihar's Sheikhpura had paid the money for a house and a land parcel in Lucknow but the deal turned out to be a scam, they said.

news.title: Right to property a constitutional right: Supreme court
news.para: A bench of justices B R Gavai and K V Viswanathan said the right to property ceased to be a fundamental right due to the Constitution (Forty-Fourth Amendment) Act, 1978, however, it continues to be a human right in a welfare state and a constitutional right under Article 300-A of the Constitution.

news.title: Gujarat: District collectors assigned to oversee administration of nine new municipal corporations
news.para: According to a Press release, with these Municipal Corporations becoming effective immediately, their existing administrative structures will be replaced, and the respective District Collectors will assume the role of Administrators for these Corporations.

news.title: Jaipur development body removes encroachment from 40 bighas of government land
news.para: Deputy inspector general of police in JDA, Kailash Chandra Bishnoi, said, "On learning that about 40 bighas of JDA-owned govt land meant for group housing scheme was encroached upon by local farmers, action was taken Thursday.

news.title: Goa government demolishes illegal structures in Cunchelim
news.para: Govt had demolished some homes in Nov, with the remaining likely to face the axe in the coming days. The occupants of the illegal structures were asked to vacate their homes.

news.title: Kanpur civic body making tiles from building material waste
news.para: The manufacturing facility established in Panki Bhau Singh became operational on Thursday and made approximately 2,500 tiles.

news.title: Karnataka cabinet gives approval for separate Dharwad civic body
news.para: The apolitical movement launched by the citizen of Dharwad, under the Agitation Committee for Separate Dharwad Municipal Corporation, which was supported by various organisations and political parties has finally been answered.

news.title: Pune civic body to install 1,700 streetlights in 34 merged areas
news.para: The areas were merged in 2017 and local self-governing bodies handed over the maintenance of civic properties, including roads and streetlights to PMC.

news.title: Tamil Nadu government approves expansion of Madurai, Trichy corporations
news.para: ​​The expansion will increase Madurai corporation's area from 147.99 square kilometres to 237.99 square kilometres. The population is correspondingly expected to grow from 18.5 lakh to nearly 20 lakh.

news.title: Chandigarh: PGI and Panjab University seek reassessment of property tax
news.para: Disagreeing with the amount of the property tax prepared by the civic body authority, both institutions stated that the prepared tax amount is not justified as per their records and thus needs a complete re-evaluation.

news.title: Indore civic body razes 50 illegal construction in Retimandi chowk
news.para: According to IMC additional commissioner Rohit Sisonia, the action, following the directives of IMC Commissioner Shivam Verma, was initiated in the Retimandi area located within IDA Scheme No. 97 Part 4.

news.title: Property registrations in Bengaluru disrupted due to sub-registrar transfers
news.para: Ringing in the New Year, several buyers and sellers had flocked to sub-registrars' offices for property transactions. However, the confusion between incumbent officers and those posted in their places affected the day's work in at least 10 sub-registrar offices.

news.title: Nashik civic body shifts building plan approvals entirely online in 2025
news.para: The process for such submissions will now be implemented online. The online system for approval of plans has been in place for the past few years.

news.title: FIR against Panchkula couple over multi-crore real estate fraud
news.para: The couple, who are alleged masterminds behind the scam, are accused of defrauding investors of over Rs 16 crore through a complex real estate and financial scheme, as per the FIR registered in Sector 7 police station.

news.title: Mumbai civic body collects Rs 5,800 crore as property tax till December-end
news.para: ​​In a release issued during the day, the Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation (BMC) said it had collected Rs 5,847 crore as property tax till December end, including Rs 433 crore in the last two days of 2024.

news.title: SC rejects Kapil Wadhawan's interim bail on medical grounds in bank loan fraud case
news.para: The CBI, however, opposed the interim bail, saying it a gross misuse of the process of law. While the regular bail application of Kapil Wadhawan is still pending before the HC, he had sought interim bail on medical grounds.

news.title: Smartworks leases 4.7 lakh sq ft office space in Gurugram
news.para: This is the fourth managed campus for Smartworks in Gurugram, in addition to the existing campuses at Golf View Corporate Towers (Golf Course Road), RK 4 Square (Cyber City), and ASF Insignia (Vatsal Valley).

news.title: NSE & BSE approve merger of three subsidiaries into JK Lakshmi Cement
news.para: As per the scheme of amalgamation, three subsidiaries namely Udaipur Cement Works, Hansdeep Industries and Trading, and Hidrive Developers and Industries are getting merged into JK Lakshmi Cement.

news.title: Thane civic body issues notices to 39 builders over air pollution norms violation
news.para: The TMC had directed 297 builders to follow dust pollution control guidelines. Of these 31 complied fully, while a cumulative fine of Rs 4 lakh was imposed on 151 builders for minor lapses.
